splits, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\iota\colon E\to M$
\end_inset

 denotes the inclusion map and 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi\colon M\to M\slash E$
\end_inset

 denotes the quotient map.
 Therefore we may choose a 
\begin_inset Formula $\widetilde{\pi}\colon M\slash E\to M$
\end_inset

