\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon E\to F$
\end_inset

 is an isomorphism of 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-modules, then 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 satisfies the same property as 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

; namely if 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 is an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module such that 
\begin_inset Formula $F\subseteq N$
\end_inset

