\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 is a direct summand of 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon E\to F$
\end_inset

 be an isomorphism, let 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\colon F\to E$
\end_inset

 denote its inverse, and let 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 be an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module such that 
\begin_inset Formula $F\subseteq N$
\end_inset

.
 We define an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-module 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(N)$
\end_inset

, where as a set we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\psi(N)=E\cup\{\psi(v)\mid v\in N\backslash F\},
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(v)$
\end_inset

 is understood to be a formal symbol if 
\begin_inset Formula $v\in N\backslash F$
\end_inset

 and is understood to be an element in 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 if 
\begin_inset Formula $v\in F$
\end_inset

.
 Here, 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 is 
\emph on
literally 
\emph default
a subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(N)$
\end_inset

.
 We extend the 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-linear structure on 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 to an 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-linear structure on 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(N)$
\end_inset

 by defining addition and scalar multiplication by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\psi(v_{1})+\psi(v_{2})=\psi(v_{1}+v_{2})\quad\text{and}\quad a\psi(v)=\psi(av).
\]

\end_inset

for all 
\begin_inset Formula $v,v_{1},v_{2}\in N\backslash F$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $a\in R$
\end_inset

.
 Defining the 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

-linear structure on 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(N)$
\end_inset

 in this way makes it so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\colon F\to E$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon E\to F$
\end_inset

 extends to an isomorphism 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi\colon N\to\psi(N)$
\end_inset

 with corresponding inverse 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon\psi(N)\to N$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
