\begin_inset Formula $\psi(N)$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(N)$
\end_inset

 is an internal direct sum, say
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\psi(N)=E\oplus K,
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 is another submodule of 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(N)$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $E\cap K=\{0\}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $E+K=\psi(N)$
\end_inset

.
 Then since 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi\colon\psi(N)\to N$
\end_inset

 is an isomorphism, we see that
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
N & =\varphi(E)\oplus\varphi(K)\\
 & =F\oplus\varphi(K).
\end{align*}

